FBIS4-45492 "jptdd027__l94070" JPRS-TDD-94-027L JPRS Narcotics 14 June 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA KAZAKHSTAN Interior Ministry Holds Antidrug Meeting in Zhambyl Oblast Interior Ministry Holds Antidrug Meeting in Zhambyl Oblast LD1406101394 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0800 GMT 14 Jun 94 LD1406101394 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network Kazakh BFN [Text] The Kazakh Interior Ministry held an itinerant session in the village of Tolebi, Zhambyl oblast, devoted to curbing drug trafficking. As is widely known, cannabis grown in Zhambyl oblast is used to produce the most widely spread drugs hashish and marijuana. The session noted that drugs smuggling routes connect the Chu valley of South Kazakhstan with China, India, Afghanistan, Italy, and France. New methods in the battle against drugs smugglers were discussed.
